 the indian trust act was formulated in 1882  when the indian trusts act 1882 was formulated section 20 notified in a  very  precise  and  detailed  way  the  financial  instruments  that  could  be  used  to invest these funds  those provisions have become completely archaic now  the time has come to remove those archaic provisions and to replace them with modern day  financial  instruments    what  we  have  said  in  effect  is  that  if  we  put  this  in place the indian trusts act will be ready for the 21st century and be  able to help the  people  who  are  the  beneficiaries  of  those  trusts    the  amendments  seek  to amend  sections  20  and  20  a  of  the  act    which  will  give  the  trustees  greater autonomy and flexibility in investments  this bill was introduced in 2009  it went to  the  standing  committee    most  of  the  recommendations  of  the  standing committee  were  accepted  and  that  is  the  amendment  that  is  now  proposed  to  be considered and passed by this august house    